  "definitions": [
    {
      "source": "EAS",
      "text": "The Greek form (Rev. 19:1, 3, 4, 6) of the Hebrew Hallelujah = Praise ye Jehovah, which begins or ends several of the psalms (106, 111, 112, 113, etc.).",
      "extracted_refs": [
        {
          "book": "Revelation",
          "chapter": 19,
          "verses": [
            1,
            3,
            4,
            6
          ],
          "verse_count": 4,
          "testament": "NT",
          "raw": "Revelation 19:1, 3, 4, 6",
          "source": "EAS"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "SMI",
      "text": "so written in (Revelation 19:6) foll., or more properly Hallelujah, praise ye Jehovah, as it is found in the margin of (Psalms 104:35; 105:45; 106; 111:1; 112:1; 113:1) comp. Psal 113:9; 115:18; 116:19, 117:2 The literal meaning of “hallelujah” sufficiently indicates the character of the Psalms in which it occurs as hymns of praise and thanksgiving.",
